PRE-INTERMEDIETE ENGLISH
USE WHO, WHOM, WHICH, THAT, WHERE
(meaning : yang)
Berfungsi sebagai pronoun
1. Who
- menjelaskan orang /people
- digunakan sebagai subject.
Example:
* Everyday I go to the office with my
friends.
* My friends work in the office.
1. Everyday I go to the office with my
friends who work in the office.
2. This is our new chief clerk, who has
just been appointed.
3. She is the operator, who runs the
machine.
4. The girl, who greeted me is the
secretary of AIT.
2. Whom
- menjelaskan orang /people
- digunakan sebagai object
- after whom selalu diikuti oleh
subject lain.
Example:
* Everyday I go to the office with my
friends.
* I hate my friends.
1. Everyday I go to the office with my
friends whom I hate.
2. This is our new chief clerk, whom we
have just appointed.
3. She is the operator, whom I know.
4. The girl, whom I greeted is the
secretary of AIT.
3. Which & That
- menjelaskan sesuatu/unliving thing
- digunakan sebagai object
- that use for both people and thing
Example:
1. I thanked the woman that helped me.
2. The book, which is on the table, is
mine.
3. The book that is on the table is mine.
4. I miss my village, which has a beautiful
beach.
4. When
- menjelaskan waktu/kapan
Example:
1. Ill never forger the day when I met
you.
5. Whose
Berarti kepunyaan (yang mempunyai)
Example:
- She is Cucu whose car is in my
house.
- I dont know the person whose hair
is long.
One
- menerangkan orang secara umum
- jika diawal kalimat menggunakan
one seterusnya harus menggunakan one tidak boleh
diselipi dengan kata lain
missal,. He, she, etc.
Example:
1. If one wants to be successful, one should
works hard.
2. One should not disturb the others if one
doesnt like to disturb oneself.
3. One can often see anothers faults, but rarely
ones own.
4. One can think badly about me but I will not
think badly about one else.
Its and Its
- Its berarti kepunyaan (benda)
sedangkan its berarti it is atau it has.
Example:
1. I saw the cat its tail was injured.
2. The engineer fixed the machine its inner part
was big problem.
3. Its a tester. (it is)
4. Its been fixed. (it has)
ADVERBS and ADJECTIVES
ADJECTIVES (kata sifat)
- Menjelaskan noun
- Selalu berada di depan noun.
- Tujuan penggunaan kata adjective
untuk lebih specification.
Example: - pretty girl
- handsome man
- lazy student
- an ugly little house
- a red leather bag
- a kind pretty girl
- a pair of smelly old black leather
bag
Example:
1. She is a pretty young girl.
2. This girl is prettier than another girl.
(Note: sebagai kalimat
perbandingan/comparative adjective diletakan setelah to be
dan diikuti kata than)
** comparative : perbandingan untuk dua
noun.
** superlative : perbandingan untuk lebih
dari dua.
Example:
Perubahan tetap:
- tall ------ taller than ------ the tallest
- slow ----- slower than ----- the
slowest
Perubahan tidak tetap:
- bad ----- worse ----- the worst
- good ----- better ----- the best
- little ----- few ----- the fewest
Note: the bisa diganti dengan kata ganti
kepunyaan
Example:
- She is my best friend.
ADVERS (kata keterangan)
- menerangkan/menjelaskan verb
(kata kerja)
- selalu mengikuti verb.
Example:
- walk slowly
- sleep soundly (tidur dengan
nyenyak)
- sing loudly
Adverb ada 3 macam:
1. Manner (keterangan cara)
Example : slowly, lovely, happily, hard, fast
- He works hard (adv.)
- He is a hard worker (adj.)
- They try to walk fast to win the
competition. (adv.)
- They are very fast in walking. (adj.)
2. Place (keterangan tempat)
* Put adverb place before adverb time.
Example : in, on, out, behind, at the back.
- The employees will go to Nongsa
Point Marina this morning.
- We met each other outside my house
last night.
- You should submit this report to
Training section by tomorrow.
3. Frequency (keterangan waktu)
* Put adverb after subject.
* Put adverb after to be
Example: tomorrow, yesterday, often, seldom,
never.
- She always goes to the office early.
- The girl who is pretty always goes to
the office early.
- They are often sad to seem cry.
- She is always late.
* Put the adverb between have/was and Verb3
Example: We have never gone to USA.
*** Adverb also to modify adjective.
Example: - She is particularly pretty.
(teristimewa)
- She is extremely happy. (terlalu)
POSITION OF ADVERBS
* We usually place definite adverbs of time
(yesterday, last week, Monday) at the end of a sentence.
Example: - I saw Miss Jones yesterday.
- I intend to go to Chicago next
week.
- I met him there on Wednesday.
* We usually place adverbs of frequency before
the main verb, except to be. The following adverbs are adverbs
frequency: often, usually, generally, ever, never, seldom,
always, rarely.
Example: - John never studied his lesson
- He always comes to his lesson
late.
- She is often late for class.
* If the sentence contains an auxiliary verb,
the adverb still goes before the main verb.
Example: - John has always been a good
student.
- He doesnt usually eat in the
cafeteria.
Either and any
- either --- two thing (milih diantara dua)
Example: - Either Ismi or Agatha can go to my
house.
- I dont like either this one or that
one.
- any --- more than two things.
Example: - Any all of you can a company me go
to Jakarta.
- If you busy you can give me any
of them.
- Either of these two patterns will
do.
- You will find any of these three
methods satisfactory.
This, that, these, those.
* this and that (singular) with these and those
(plural) must agree with their nouns in number.
Example: - We have had this sort (these sorts)
of excuse before.
- They prefer that type (those
types) of desk.
VERBS
Ssingular ----Vs/es
Take a verb in singular.
1. Each (setiap)
Example: - Each of my friends likes ice cream.
- Each of us always works hard to
have a better position in the work place.
2. Everyone
Example: - Everyone hates me. I dont have any
friend (s).
Note: jika dalam bentuk ? any selalu diikuti
plural.
- Do you have any books?
- I dont have any book (s). Kalimat
negativenya.
3. either --- either .. or . (salah satu)
- Wida can stay in my house.
- Ismi can stay in my house.
* Either Wida or Ismi can stay in my house.
* I will go to either Agathas house or Ismis
house.
Penggunaan lainnya yang berarti juga.
* I dont like coffee and Dewi doesnt either.
4. neither --- neither nor (tak
satupun)
* Neither the two girls can go to my house.
* Neither those two reports are correct.
Neither selalu diikuti oleh verb singular
(Vs/es)) kecuali menggunakan modal.
* Neither Wida nor Ismi can stay in my house.
~ Perubahan verb di dalam kalimat present
tense dipengaruhi oleh S and Time.
>>>> Subject
a. Countable; book, pen, egg, desk S + V s/es
Example: - My book is red.
- My books are red.
- She goes to school
- I go to school
b. Uncountable: sugar, hair, air
Example: - Sugar is in my bag.
1. Subject in singular >>> S + V s/es
Subject in plural >>> S + V
Other examples:
- Deposits, including bank account
worth a lot.
- Sugar, together with salt is in my
bag
- Meat and vegetable is always in my
freeze.
Note: Jika 2 kata yang sama disambung
dengan and maka diikuti oleh Verb in singular tapi jika tidak
dihubungkan dengan kata and maka diikuti oleh Verb in
plural.
2. either, any, neither, whatever, whoever,
everything, anything, each.
Example:
- Anything is all right for me.
- Whatever happens to us, we will
finish at 12 AM.
- Whoever is the manager, I respect
the decision.
- Either of these two reports is wrong.
- Any of these five pencils is broken.
- Neither the two advice helps me.
- Everything has destroyed nothing is
left.
- Each of the operators has a wrist
strap.
3. Collective noun
Example:
- The firm has five managers.
- The firm agree with our offer
(collective noun yang menjelaskan orang-orangnya)
KALIMAT PASIF ( PASSIVE SENTENCES )
Example Active sentences:
- I read books everyday. (V 1)
- I read books yesterday. (V 2)
- I can read 10 books.
- I will read 10 books.
- I have read books. (V3)
RUMUS
To be + V3
Modal be + V3
Have/has been + V3
Kalimat passivenya:
- Books are read by me everyday.
- Books were read by me yesterday.
- 10 books can be read by me.
- 10 books will be read by me.
- Books have been read by me.
Please
Kata seru: please selalu diikuti verb 1.
* Please prepare for everything.
1. PRESENT PERFECT TENSE.
1. Indicates an action that has happened at an
indefinite (Waktu yang tak tentu) time in the past.
waktu yang disebutkan: a week ago
RUMUS: S + have/has + V3
Example:
- I have studied English.
- She has taken a bath.
2. Indicate an action that was repeated several
times in the past. (rumus sama)
Example:
- We have conducted the meeting from time to
time but we still cannot get the agreement.
3. Indicates an action that began in the past
and has continued up to now. (rumus sama)
Example:
- We have left our workplace for 1 hour.
2. PRESENT PERFECT PROGRESIVE
(CONTINUES) TENSE
1. To indicates the duration of an activity began
in the past an continues to present.
Example:
- We have been studying English for
on moth.
- Ismi has been sick since this
morning.
2. When no specific time mentioned, it
expresses a general activity in progress recently lately.
Perbedaan penggunaan kata since and for
Example:
- I have studied English since 1999
(sejak)
- I have studied English for 5 years
(selama)
Yet and already
Example:
- I havent finished yet. (not yet)
- Have you already completed your
homework?
- We have done our task already.
3. PRESENT PERFECT TENSE (Tidak
menyebutkan waktu.)
RUMUS: S + had + V3 + O
Example:
- Agatha had gone home when I
arrived to Widas house. (verb 2 in simple past)
- Weni had finished her cooking the
time Basa went to her house.
- Gayatri and Dewi had completed the
tests when Ani called them to club.
Note: 2 kejadian
- I had taken my breakfast when Cucu
arrived.
- I had had my breakfast when Cucu
arrived.
